Lastly, on Windows you need to install USB drivers - this is done with the 
\f1\b mchelper
\f0\b0  installer.  Head to www.makingthings.com/resources/downloads and grab the latest version of mchelper, and run the installer.  It's best to do this before plugging in your Make Controller for the first time - otherwise, Windows likes to create a stub of a USB device in the device manager that then usually needs to be deleted.  OS X does not require a driver installation.\
